    "department": "GPX",
    "description": "ABOUT JUNIPER SQUARE\n\nOur mission is to unlock the full potential of private markets. Privately owned assets like commercial real estate, private equity, and venture capital make up half of our financial ecosystem yet remain inaccessible to most people. We are digitizing these markets, and as a result, bringing efficiency, transparency, and access to one of the most productive corners of our financial ecosystem. If you care about making the world a better place by making markets work better through technology – all while contributing as a member of a values-driven organization – we want to hear from you. \n\nJuniper Square offers employees a variety of ways to work, ranging from a fully remote experience to working full-time in one of our physical offices. We invest heavily in digital-first https://blog.junipersquare.com/juniper-square-ponders-future-of-office-with-digital-first-hybrid-workplace-strategy/ operations, allowing our teams to collaborate effectively across 27 U.S. states, 2 Canadian Provinces, India, Luxembourg, and England. We also have physical offices in San Francisco, New York City, Mumbai and Bangalore for employees who prefer to work in an office some or all of the time.\n\n\nABOUT YOUR ROLE\n\nWe are looking for a Technical Consultant to play a pivotal role in empowering our clients to maximize the value of our innovative investment management platform. You'll be a trusted advisor, driving successful implementations and fostering long-term customer relationships by leveraging your deep product knowledge and industry insights. This is an opportunity to directly impact how our clients operate, transforming their processes and enhancing their investor experience.\n\nAs a Technical Consultant, you will design, develop, and deliver tailored solutions that address our clients' unique business challenges. You'll partner closely with clients across their organizations, understanding their workflows and guiding them towards more efficient and effective practices. Your expertise will be instrumental in ensuring seamless adoption, driving feature utilization, and achieving optimal business outcomes.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Strategic Consultation: Partner with clients to understand their strategic goals, business drivers, and desired outcomes, crafting customized adoption plans that align with their objectives.\n\n - Solution Delivery: Lead the design and implementation of solutions, ensuring timely execution and overcoming potential constraints to drive positive results.\n\n - Training \u0026 Enablement: Develop and deliver comprehensive training programs for diverse user groups, simplifying complex technical concepts for varying levels of expertise.\n\n - Technical Expertise: Serve as a subject matter expert, maintaining a deep understanding of product functionality, industry best practices, and customer behaviors.\n\n - Cross-Functional Collaboration: Partner with Project Management, Customer Success, Service and Support, and Product Development teams to resolve complex issues and influence product roadmap decisions.\n\n - Process Optimization: Develop and implement standard operating procedures to enhance the efficiency and effectiveness of the Technical Consulting Team.\n\n - Knowledge Sharing: Create and maintain documentation on product and procedural best practices, ensuring consistent messaging across the organization.\n\n\nQUALIFICATIONS\n\n - Minimum of 2 years of experience working with clients within the investment management industry.\n\n - Proven ability to lead client-facing meetings and presentations, including executive-level audiences.\n\n - Exceptional analytical, interpersonal, and communication skills (written and verbal).\n\n - Strong problem-solving abilities and a proactive approach to identifying and implementing process improvements.\n\n - Ability to work independently with minimal supervision and thrive in a collaborative team environment.\n\n - Willingness to travel nationally up to 10% as needed.\n\n - Technical experience in working with API implementations is a plus\n\n - Previous consulting experience helping customers achieve outcomes in a technical manner\n\n - Bachelor’s degree or equivalent professional experience.\n\n\nCOMPENSATION\n\nCompensation for this position includes a base salary and a variety of benefits. The U.S. base salary range for this role is $90,000 - $110,000. Actual base salaries will be based on candidate-specific factors, including experience, skillset, and location, and local minimum pay requirements as applicable.\n\nBenefits include:\n\n - Health, dental, and vision care for you and your family\n\n - Life insurance\n\n - Mental wellness coverage\n\n - Fertility and growing family support\n\n - Flex Time Off in addition to company paid holidays\n\n - Paid family leave, medical leave, and bereavement leave policies\n\n - Retirement saving plans\n\n - Allowance to customize your work and technology setup at home\n\n - Annual professional development stipend\n\nYour recruiter can provide additional details about compensation and benefits.\n\n#experiencedprofessional\n\n#LI-AM\n\n#LI-Remote\n\n#Juniper-US",
